File: Denel is battling to stay afloat after reporting a R1.7-billion loss. JOHANNESBURG - State-owned arms manufacturer, Denel, can only afford to pay its employees 85 percent of their salaries this month. In a statement sent out to employees, the group's CEO, Daniel du Toit, says this is due to the company's ongoing liquidity challenges. WATCH: Denel in the spotlight at state capture inquiry Management says it’s working tirelessly to ensure the delayed portion of salaries will be reimbursed as soon as possible. They also apologised for the late communication. The company says it had no alternative but to go this route.